$ $ORACLE_HOME/root.sh

This script must be run as root to complete an installation.

The content of `root.sh` is modified when other products are installed into an Oracle home. Oracle therefore recommends to back up this script after completing an installation.

This script runs script such as
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/install/utl/rootmacro_sh`
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/install/utl/rootinstall_sh`
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/install/root_schagent_sh`
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/network/install/sqlnet/setowner_sh`
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/rdbms/install/rootadd_rdbms_sh`
  • `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/rdbms/install/rootadd_filemap_sh`

sa:


 `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oraInventory/orainstRoot_sh`

 `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n`

